Here is an example of how you can draw a chessboard in LATEX using the `pgfs` package:
```
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{pgfs}
\begin{document}
\begin{pgfsplot}[fsize=16]{chessboard}
  \pgfsset{chessboard}{file=board.pgfs}
\end{pgfsplot}
\end{document}
```
This code will use the `pgfs` package to load the "board.pgfs" file, which is assumed to contain the FEN notation of the chessboard. The `pgfsplot` environment is used to load the board file and display the chessboard. The `fsize` option is used to specify the size of the board in points.
